http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Ghee-manufacturing-units-raided-in-AP/article13989978.ece

The Food Safety Department on Friday conducted raids at ghee manufacturing units across the State and seized stock from those units.Special teams led by four Zonal Officers raided the units, collected 30 samples and sent those to the State Food Laboratory in Hyderabad for analysis. “We will launch prosecution in the Judicial Magisterial First Class Court against the manufacturers, if they are found to be involved in the adulteration of ghee,” said Joint Food Controller K.N. Swaroop.He said that the raids were carried out after receiving complaints that adulterated ghee sachets were being sold in the market.According to Mr. Swaroop, Srikakulam, Visakhapatnam and Vizianagaram districts come under the Zone-I, while East and West Godavari and Krishna under Zone-II and Guntur, Prakasam and Nellore under Zone-III.